h3. Summary
A text field does not appear in the property panel of the macro

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Add following to parameter description in atlassian-connect.json:{code:javascript}
        "propertyPanel": {
          "url": "/render/1.0/mathinline-editor-panel",
          "controls": [
            {
              "type": "button",
              "label": { "value": "My Custom Control 0" },
              "key": "my-custom-control-0"
            }
          ]
        }
{code}
# A button appears in the macro property panel
# Change the description text to: {code:javascript}
        "propertyPanel": {
          "url": "/render/1.0/mathinline-editor-panel",
          "controls": [
            {
              "key": "mathinline-panel-body",
              "macroParameter": "body",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
{code}
# The button is gone, but no text control appears. However, there is still a gap between the Edit and Remove buttons.

h3. Expected Results
Text box on property panel

h3. Actual Results
No text box, only a small gap where it should be

 !Missing TextControl.jpg|thumbnail!

h3. Summary
Contents of Confluence Questions are not imported into Confluence server when doing a Confluence Cloud - Server migration

Confluence Questions content should be included in Full Export: https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CQ-186

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Have a Cloud instance with Confluence Questions contents
# Perform site backup
# Import into Confluence server

h3. Expected Results
# All contents are migrated including Confluence Questions content

h3. Actual Results
Confluence Questions content are not imported

h3. Notes
For "Questions" and "Answers", and "Comments" they are included in the import and are inside the CONTENT table with the following attributes:
{code}
Question
ac:com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:question

Answer
ac:com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:answer

Comment
NULL
{code}

These content does not recognized by server as this is what the plugin key should be in Server:
{code}
Question
com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:question

Answer
com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:answer

Comment
com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:comment
{code}

h3.Workaround
The following will restore all questions and answers and comments, however it will not restore others (Such as Votes and Accepted answers, etc)
{code}
//update the plugin keys for Questions and Answers
update content  set PLUGINKEY = 'com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:answer' where  pluginkey ='ac:com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:answer';
update content  set PLUGINKEY = 'com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:question' where  pluginkey ='ac:com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:question';

//This query is to change the Questions that the answer is tied to from the column PAGEID(in Cloud) to PARENTCCID(in server)
update content set PARENTCCID = PAGEID where PLUGINKEY = 'com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:answer' AND PAGEID IS NOT NULL;

//This query is to cleanup the PAGEID
update content set PAGEID = NULL where PLUGINKEY = 'com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:answer';
{code}

For restoring Comments which is a trickier task:
{code}
//this is to find the contentIDs of the questions, and to confirm
SELECT contentid FROM CONTENT where PLUGINKEY =  'com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:question';

//Create a new temp table to insert the Comment data gathered above
CREATE TABLE TEMPCONTENT LIKE CONTENT;
INSERT INTO TEMPCONTENT SELECT * from CONTENT where CONTENTTYPE = 'COMMENT' and PAGEID in (SELECT contentid FROM CONTENT where PLUGINKEY =  'com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:question');

//Make adjustments in the Content table
UPDATE CONTENT SET CONTENTTYPE = 'CUSTOM' WHERE CONTENTID IN (SELECT CONTENTID FROM TEMPCONTENT);
UPDATE CONTENT SET PLUGINKEY = 'com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:comment' WHERE CONTENTID IN (SELECT CONTENTID FROM TEMPCONTENT);
UPDATE CONTENT SET PARENTCCID = PAGEID WHERE CONTENTID IN (SELECT CONTENTID FROM TEMPCONTENT) AND PAGEID IS NOT NULL;

//This query is to cleanup the PAGEID
update content set PAGEID = NULL where PLUGINKEY = 'com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:comment';

DROP TABLE TEMPCONTENT;
{code}
(!) Please always backup your database before performing any alteration in the database side.

